Located in the well-known Little Italy of the Bronx. António's Trattoria is surrounded by a multitude of incredible cuisine experiences.  As we are all aware, the indoor dining room took a breath and makeshift outdoor shelters afflicted the area. Some are better than others, but we all know that in these cold, dry months, a ceiling light with an open door will not keep your lower extremities warm.  However, AT had a brilliant and groundbreaking idea. Anchor three transparent yurts with zipped entry doors from floor to ceiling coupled with heat lamps that sit at eye and arrow level - protection from many cruel elements of winter. You are now comfortable for about 59 minutes, giving you ample time to enjoy a crunchy Caesar salad and a large wood-fired margarita pizza.  As we waited for the cheque, we had a cup of coffee to circulate our blood. In these dark days, it feels like eating under the stars on Mars. This arrangement transformed our dismal day into a place of eclectic restoration.  So if you feel sad and have a few extra dollars to draw from your inner child - welcome to winter camp! The staff felt like camp instructors watching us every five minutes.  Kudos to that institution for finding ways to bring us back.

I'm not one to review but this place earned it. My family and I went to this restaurant  (July 11th) and we were greeted and sat down outside,then they unexpected happened. The most random rain, I thought I was in the Caribbean with the way it was raining and how windy it was. Anyway, I wanted to try a different Italian restaurant besides patricias on Morris Park, the food there has become bland, but back to Antonio's. Once it started to rain they quickly rushed everyone inside, for that I was grateful because it was my baby's first time out in a while and I did not want him to get wet with the rain. They allowed those who had already ordered to sit inside and finish their food, and honestly I thought that was very nice of them being the circumstance NY is in right now. So we sat down and ordered, I ordered the calamari for appetizer and Alfredo with chicken and my partner ordered penne allá vodka. Delicious, that's it. Real pasta btw, so good I had to take some home with me to indulge later when my baby went to sleep lol, the service was amazing everyone in there was very nice and not just because it rained and they wanted to accommodate everyone, but because I genuinely could tell that this is who they are, they care about their customers and with that being said, they have another customer coming back soon, of course next time I'll check the weather in case there's any hurricanes stopping by. I didn't get anyone's name, but to everyone on that afternoon/evening shift, thank you! Oh and they give hand sanitizer once you sit! Another plus!

On the up side, the wine and Nutella calzone I shared were excellent. The cannoli are from Artuso, which are fab (but it’s down the block so just buy them there along with some sfogliatelle — you won’t be sorry). I would go back to try the pizza and homemade pasta, especially because their fresh mozzarella is from Casa (THE best). That fare might win me over completely to this place. But this first experience was a bit more hype than heavenly Italian.

Everything came out in reasonable timing and the restaurant had no issues accommodating my vegan diet by adding extra veggies to my pizza and keeping off the cheese. The portion sizes are pretty large so we shared an endive salad. My partner got the steak which was reasonable priced and HUGE!  After dinner, we stopped for Limoncello’s (spelling) and Frangelico’a at the bar in the other room. JOHN was bartending and took wonderful care of us. He was very attentive to the whole bar and we have no complaints. There was an older man there that was really funny as well but we did not get his name.  Let me just say that the whole atmosphere was so warm and welcoming. Very family friendly environment and you could tell many of the locals and real Italians frequented. A lot of smiles and laughter from both the staff and guests. Thank you for providing such an exceptional experience! We will most definitely return when we are in the area. :) 5/5

Very friendly wait staff and bar tender and lots of staff... No waiting for anything! Spouse's coffee was good, my house red wine was very, very good. Baked clams appetizer with the chunky bread was fabulous. Veal saltimbocca entree was enormous and absolutely perfect. Side of ziti was ok. Spouse tried the pork chop with hot cherry peppers and side of green beans. Came with serving of polenta as well. Oh my, it was fabulous! The cherry peppers were a bit too hot for me, but flavors blended wonderfully and he was delighted. The green beans were bursting with buttery/garlicky flavour and cooked just enough to be crisp/ tender. We were too full to order dessert, darn it, but my apres cappachino was rich and wonderful. Left Antonio's wishing I lived in NYC just so I could return and try other dishes and the Italian cheesecake!
